The paper deals with the analysis of network structures and their Laplacian eigenvalues, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several CS sub-categories. The use of breath-first search (BFS) to define local subgraphs suggests that the paper may belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The study of Laplacian eigenvalues also suggests that the paper may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SD (Systems and Control). The proposed techniques for estimating spectral properties from random local subgraphs suggest that the paper may belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
